The paper discusses cross-modal retrieval, which involves retrieving data of one modality based on a query of another modality. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including information retrieval (cs.IR), computer vision (cs.CV), multimedia (cs.MM), natural language processing (cs.CL), and machine learning (cs.LG). Given that the paper covers both real-valued and binary representation learning methods, it is likely to be relevant to multiple sub-categories. However, based on the content of the paper, we believe that cs.IR and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.MM, cs.CL, and cs.LG.
